definitions.definition: Pertaining to a nation or country, especially as a whole; affecting, shared by, or existing throughout all of a nation.
examples: a national assembly · on the front page of every national newspaper
Import tariffs were raised for the national interest.

definitions.definition: Belonging to or characteristic of a specific nation or country, as opposed to others.
examples: this is their national dish · our national tendency to laugh at the French

main_definition: Pertaining to a nation or country, especially as a whole; affecting, shared by, or existing throughout all of a nation. [from 16th c.]
secondary_definitions: Belonging to or characteristic of a specific nation or country, as opposed to others. [from 17th c.]
